behave /bɪˈheɪv/

(behaving,behaved,behaves) 

1. V-I The way that you behave is the way that you do and say things, and the things that you do and say. 行为; 表现 

例： I couldn't believe these people were behaving in this way. 我无法相信这些人竟这样行事。 

2. V-T/V-I If you behave or behave yourself , you act in the way that people think is correct and proper. 使…规矩; 规矩地行事 

例： You have to behave. 你得守规矩。 

3. V-I In science, the way that something behaves is the things that it does. (科学领域) 运动表现 

例： Under certain conditions, electrons can behave like waves rather than particles. 在某些条件下，电子能像波而不是粒子那样运动。

